.TH GIT-PR-OPEN 1 "2026-06-14" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-open \- push a branch and create a pull request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-open
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-open
pushes the current branch with upstream tracking and creates a GitHub pull
request without interactive prompts.
.PP
The command refuses dirty worktrees, refuses to open a pull request from the
base branch itself, fetches the base remote, and rejects a stale local base
branch when the local base branch differs from its remote-tracking branch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-t, \-\-title " title
Pull request title. Required unless a
.B \-\-fill
mode is used.
.TP
.BI "\-b, \-\-body " body
Pull request body.
.TP
.BI "\-F, \-\-body-file " file
Read pull request body from file.
.TP
.BI "\-B, \-\-base " branch
Base branch. Defaults to the repository default branch.
.TP
.BI "\-H, \-\-head " branch
Head branch name for GitHub. Defaults to the current branch.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-draft
Create a draft pull request.
.TP
.BR \-\-fill ", " \-\-fill-first ", " \-\-fill-verbose
Use GitHub CLI commit-derived title and body modes.
.TP
.B \-\-no-maintainer-edit
Disable maintainer edits.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry-run
Print actions without changing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Pull request was created, or dry-run completed.
.TP
.B 1
Pull request creation failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-checks (1),
.BR git-pr-ready (1)
